==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Men
<hw>Men</hw>, <pos>pron.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>me</ets>, <ets>men</ets>.
⟦ldquo⟧Not the plural of <ets>man</ets>, but a weakened form of the word
<ets>man</ets> itself.⟦rdquo⟧ <ets>Skeat</ets>.]</ety> <def>A man; one;
-- used with a verb in the singular, and corresponding to the present
indefinite <xex>one</xex> or <xex>they</xex>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Piers Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Men</qex> moot give silver to the poure friars.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A privy thief, <qex>men</qex> clepeth death.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Menaccanite</ent>⟦br⟧
